## Sample Naming

### Dataset 1

| Channel | Sample |
| ------- | ------ |
| CH2     | FL2-F  |
| CH3     | GN2-2  |

### Dataset 2

| Channel | Sample |
| ------- | ------ |
| CH2     | GN2-3  |
| CH3     | FL2C3  |

---

## Recommended Analysis Path

1. Run Notebook 1 to generate processed MR datasets.
2. Run Notebook 2 to inspect raw MR behavior.
3. Run Notebook 3 to obtain traditional transport parameters.
4. Run Notebook 4 to compare advanced physical models.
5. Use Notebook 4 trend plots for publication-quality comparisons.

---

## Typical Output Parameters

### Low-Field Transport

* Quadratic mobility-like coefficient
* Sondheimer mobility-like coefficient
* Characteristic field

[
B_c
===

\frac{1}{b}
]

### High-Field Transport

* Linear MR slope

### Model Quality

* Low-field (R^2)
* High-field (R^2)
* Global (R^2)

