---

## Notes

The Sondheimer model is used here as an empirical parameterization of low-field orbital magnetoresistance. The extracted mobility-like parameters should be interpreted as effective fitting parameters rather than direct carrier mobilities unless independently validated by Hall measurements.

The workflow is designed for comparative analysis between nanowire-array samples and is particularly useful for identifying transitions between low-field orbital magnetoresistance and high-field linear magnetoresistance.
